{% embed "@molecules/components/component-scrollspy-section/_component-scrollspy-section-main.twig" with
    {
        "component_scrollspy_section_id": "section-components-molecules-navigation"
    }
%}
    {% block component_scrollspy_section_content %}
        <h3>Navigation</h3>
        <p>Navigation elements are crucial to any website as they allow users to move between site pages. NDS offers several patterns to make navigation easy and policy-compliant.</p>
        <h4>Primary Navigation</h4>
        <p>Primary navigation is used to move between the major sections of your website. NDS recommends including primary navigation directly below the header of your site for easiest access.</p>
        <p></p>
        {% embed "@molecules/components/component-snippet/_component-snippet-main.twig" with
            {
                "component_snippet_classes": "component--snippet--primary-navigation"
            }
        %}
            {% block component_snippet_code %}
                {% include "@nds/02-molecules/navigation/navigation-primary/demo/navigation-primary.twig" %}
            {% endblock %}
            {% block component_snippet_pattern_info %}
                <h5>Overview</h5>
                <p>Although it is possible to use the NDS out of the box component for Priary Navigation, it is likely you will need to replicate the pattern for your particular site due to the unique nature of different websites. To make your own custom pattern, simply copy the navigation-primary component from inside the 00-nds/ directory, and paste it into your 02-molecules/ directory. Then you can freely make changes to the component without altering the original NDS component.</p>
                <p>You will need to supply the primary navigation pattern with content using the "navigation_primary_content" block. You can pass links or dropdown markup, using the proper NDS structure and classes. <strong>Reference the demo pattern to see examples of links and dropdowns with the proper structure and classes.</strong></p>
                <h5>Blocks</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>&#123;% block navigation_primary_content %&#125;: The block holding the navigation markup.</li>
                </ul>
                <h5>Parameters</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>navigation_primary_classes: Additional classes for the navigation component.</li>
                    <li>navigation_primary_id: Navigation component ID.</li>
                </ul>
            {% endblock %}
        {% endembed %}

        <h4>Breadcrumbs</h4>
        <p>Breadcrumbs are used to help users identify where they are within the menu sytem of the site. Breadcrumbs will typically appear on pages one level deep in the menu system.</p>
        {% include "@atoms/text/text-uswds/_text-uswds-main.twig" with
            {
                "text_uswds_component_name": "Breadcrumbs",
                "text_uswds_href": "https://designsystem.digital.gov/components/breadcrumb/"
            }
        %}
        {% embed "@molecules/components/component-snippet/_component-snippet-main.twig" %}
            {% block component_snippet_code %}
                {% include "@nds/02-molecules/navigation/navigation-breadcrumbs/demo/navigation-breadcrumbs.twig" %}
            {% endblock %}
            {% block component_snippet_pattern_info %}
                <h5>Parameters</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>navigation_breadcrumbs_classes: Additional classes for the navigation component.</li>
                    <li>navigation_breadcrumbs_id: Navigation component ID.</li>
                    <li>navigation_breadcrumbs_data: An array of breadcrumb objects. Structure: {"text": "", "href": "", "routeName": ""}. The "href" key can be empty. The "routeName" key should be empty unless using Drupal.</li>
                    <li>navigation_breadcrumbs_icon_weight: Font Awesome icon weight. Options: 'r', 's' (Default), 'b', 'l' (Pro-Only), 'd' (Pro-Only).</li>
                </ul>
                <h5>Includes</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Atoms -> Icons -> icon-default</li>
                </ul>
            {% endblock %}
        {% endembed %}

        <h4>Pagination</h4>
        <p>Pagination helps separate long lists of content, such as search results, into separate pages to improve content readability and findability. Pagination is typically found below the content listing.</p>
        {% embed "@molecules/components/component-snippet/_component-snippet-main.twig" %}
            {% block component_snippet_code %}
                {% include "@nds/02-molecules/navigation/navigation-pagination/demo/navigation-pagination.twig" %}
            {% endblock %}
            {% block component_snippet_pattern_info %}
                <h5>Overview</h5>
                <p>The markup for the pagination buttons is based on the Drupal implementation. The Pagination component mostly serves as a wrapper to pass pagination butotn markup to the "navigation_pagination_content" block. Refer to the demo for the proper structure and classes of the pagination buttons.</p>
                <h5>Blocks</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>&#123;% block navigation_pagination_content %&#125;: The block holding the pagination markup.</li>
                </ul>
                <h5>Parameters</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>navigation_pagination_classes: Additional classes for the navigation component.</li>
                    <li>navigation_pagination_id: Navigation component ID.</li>
                </ul>
            {% endblock %}
        {% endembed %}

        <h4>Side Drawer (Mobile Menu)</h4>
        <p>When viewing websites on mobile devices, the site navigation often changes to accommodate the smaller screen size. NDS offers a "drawer" style slide out menu where menu links can be added. NDS has pre-made JavaScript functionality that toggles the drawer open and closed on click of a button with an ID of "global-mobile-menu."</p>
        {% embed "@molecules/components/component-snippet/_component-snippet-main.twig" with
            {
                "component_snippet_show_rendered": "no"
            }
        %}
            {% block component_snippet_code %}
                {% include "@nds/02-molecules/navigation/navigation-drawer/demo/navigation-drawer.twig" with
                    {
                        "navigation_drawer_id": "side-drawer"
                    }
                %}
            {% endblock %}
        {% endembed %}

        <h4>Mobile Rail</h4>
        <p>This simple component helps transition your site from a desktop layout to mobile by collapsing the local navigation (or whatever is wrapped) into a dropdown.</p>
        {% embed "@molecules/components/component-snippet/_component-snippet-main.twig" %}
            {% block component_snippet_code %}
                {% include "@nds/02-molecules/navigation/navigation-mobile-rail/demo/navigation-mobile-rail.twig" %}
            {% endblock %}
        {% endembed %}
    {% endblock %}
{% endembed %}
